        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 10:49PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1049 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Amarillo, moving northwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Lake Tanglewood, Washburn, Valley De Oro, and Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
